abstract: The former president challenged young activists for being judgmental. “You should get over that quickly,” he said.
snippet: The former president challenged young activists for being judgmental. “You should get over that quickly,” he said.
lead_paragraph: Former President Barack Obama made a rare foray into the cultural conversation this week, objecting to the prevalence of “call-out culture” and “wokeness” during an interview about youth activism at the Obama Foundation summit on Tuesday.

abstract: The California senator’s fund-raising struggles are prompting her to reboot her campaign with a focus on Iowa.
snippet: The California senator’s fund-raising struggles are prompting her to reboot her campaign with a focus on Iowa.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California took her most drastic action yet on Wednesday to salvage her once-promising, now-languishing presidential bid, laying off staff members at her Baltimore headquarters and elsewhere, and redeploying others to Iowa, where she is looking to rejuvenate her campaign.

headline_main: Kamala Harris Campaign Cuts Staff in Effort to Keep Up With Top Rivals
headline_print_headline: Harris Cuts Staff in Effort to Revive Bid
byline_original: By Astead W. Herndon and Shane Goldmacher

abstract: Trailing in the money race, tripped up by their own missteps and perceived by some as less electable, nonwhite candidates find themselves well back of the leaders.
snippet: Trailing in the money race, tripped up by their own missteps and perceived by some as less electable, nonwhite candidates find themselves well back of the leaders.
lead_paragraph: When the Democratic primary contest began last winter, it featured the most racially diverse field in history, with two black senators, a Latino former cabinet secretary, an Asian-American businessman and the first American Samoan elected to Congress. But 10 months later, the Democratic field has a top tier of four white candidates, three of them men.

headline_main: Democrats Have the Most Racially Diverse Field Ever. The Top Tier Is All White.
headline_print_headline: Democrats Have Diverse Field, But the Top Tier Is All White
byline_original: By Astead W. Herndon and Jonathan Martin

abstract: One day after President Trump hailed his own record on criminal justice and belittled Barack Obama’s, Democrats hit back at his record and history of racial demagogy.
snippet: One day after President Trump hailed his own record on criminal justice and belittled Barack Obama’s, Democrats hit back at his record and history of racial demagogy.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — One day after President Trump claimed he had done more for black voters than the Obama administration had, several Democratic presidential candidates spoke at the same historically black college on Saturday and issued a blistering rebuke of both the president and the event’s organizers — whom they accused of giving Mr. Trump an undeserved platform.

abstract: The sixth debate, hosted by PBS NewsHour and Politico, will be held at U.C.L.A. on Dec. 19.
snippet: The sixth debate, hosted by PBS NewsHour and Politico, will be held at U.C.L.A. on Dec. 19.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic National Committee announced on Friday that the sixth Democratic primary debate would be held in December at the University of California, Los Angeles, while ratcheting up the polling and donor criteria for candidates to qualify for a coveted spot onstage.

headline_main: California, Tulsi Gabbard, Betsy DeVos: Your Friday Briefing

abstract: The decision to focus on her presidential campaign, despite low polling numbers, is likely to fuel speculation that she may be preparing a third-party bid.
snippet: The decision to focus on her presidential campaign, despite low polling numbers, is likely to fuel speculation that she may be preparing a third-party bid.
lead_paragraph: Representative Tulsi Gabbard of Hawaii, who has remained in the race for the Democratic presidential nomination even as her bid has failed to gain much traction in polls, announced Friday that she would not seek a fifth term in Congress.
